Package com.qoretechnologies.qorus.workflow

Class DynamicDataHelper

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.qore.jni.QoreObjectWrapper
      • com.qoretechnologies.qorus.workflow.WorkflowDataHelper
        • com.qoretechnologies.qorus.workflow.DynamicDataHelper
  • public class DynamicDataHelper
extends WorkflowDataHelper
    Java wrapper for the OMQ::UserApi::Workflow::DynamicDataHelper "DynamicDataHelper" class in Qorus This class is a helper class that allows dynamicdata "workflow dynamic data" to be read and updated atomically; the write lock for the data is grabbed in the constructor and released in the destructor Calls to the following workflow API functions related to dynamicdata "workflow dynamic data" can be made normally while this object exists and the write lock is held; the functions are aware of and automatically use the write lock held by this object:
    • WorkflowApi.deleteDynamicDataKey()
    • WorkflowApi.getDynamicData()
    • WorkflowApi.updateDynamicData()
    The %Qore-language destructor is run at the end of the Java step execution, after the step returns to Qorus.
